#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "now recruiting"
msgstr "reclutando ahora"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"Fly with a corp that <span class=\"text-gold\">turns data into action</span>."
msgstr ""
"Vuela con una corp que <span class=\"text-gold\">convierte los datos en "
"acción</span>."

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"\n"
"        Whether you're a day-old capsuleer or a veteran looking for a "
"sharper home, Forças Armadas\n"
"        runs fleets, builds capitals, and backs every pilot with tooling "
"that tells you exactly what\n"
"        to fly, train, and build next. No spreadsheets. No guesswork.\n"
"      "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"        Ya seas un capsulero de un día o un veterano en busca de un hogar "
"más afilado, Forças Armadas\n"
"        organiza flotas, construye capitals y respalda a cada piloto con "
"herramientas que te dicen exactamente qué\n"
"        volar, entrenar y construir a continuación. Sin hojas de cálculo. "
"Sin conjeturas.\n"
"      "

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "You're signed in — ping a recruiter in-game"
msgstr "Has iniciado sesión — avisa a un reclutador en el juego"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Log in with EVE to apply"
msgstr "Inicia sesión con EVE para postularte"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "See our killboard"
msgstr "Mira nuestro killboard"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "What you get as a member"
msgstr "Lo que obtienes como miembro"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Fleet PvP"
msgstr "PvP de flota"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"Doctrine fleets with ships and SRP support — show up, undock, get on "
"killmails."
msgstr ""
"Flotas de doctrine con naves y soporte de SRP — preséntate, sal de la "
"estación y súmate a los killmails."

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Industry &amp; building"
msgstr "Industria &amp; construcción"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"From frigates to capitals — full bills of materials, build-vs-buy, and "
"shared projects."
msgstr ""
"Desde fragatas hasta capitals — listas de materiales completas, construir-vs-"
"comprar y proyectos compartidos."

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "New-pilot friendly"
msgstr "Ideal para pilotos nuevos"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"A guided skill path, starter doctrines, and patient people. Alpha clones "
"welcome."
msgstr ""
"Una ruta de habilidades guiada, doctrines de inicio y gente paciente. Clones "
"Alpha bienvenidos."

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Tools that help"
msgstr "Herramientas que ayudan"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"This very platform: \"can I fly this?\", what to train, and where the corp "
"needs you."
msgstr ""
"Esta misma plataforma: \"¿puedo volar esto?\", qué entrenar y dónde te "
"necesita la corp."

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "How to join"
msgstr "Cómo unirse"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"text-ink\">Log in with EVE SSO.</span> We only ever read "
"public data to start — no password is stored."
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"text-ink\">Inicia sesión con EVE SSO.</span> Al principio solo "
"leemos datos públicos: no se guarda ninguna contraseña."

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"text-ink\">Get a personalised plan.</span> The app shows your "
"readiness and a starter skill path the moment you connect."
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"text-ink\">Consigue un plan personalizado.</span> La app "
"muestra tu preparación y una ruta de skills inicial en cuanto te conectas."

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"text-ink\">Talk to a recruiter in-game</span> and apply to the "
"corp. Once you're verified, every member tool unlocks."
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"text-ink\">Habla con un reclutador dentro del juego</span> y "
"solicita entrar en la corp. Una vez verificado, se desbloquea cada "
"herramienta de miembro."

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Who we're looking for"
msgstr "A quién buscamos"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Pilots who want to improve — kills, skills, or ISK."
msgstr "Pilotos que quieren mejorar: kills, skills o ISK."

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Brand-new players willing to learn (we'll teach)."
msgstr ""
"Jugadores totalmente nuevos dispuestos a aprender (nosotros enseñamos)."

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Builders and logistics pilots who keep fleets supplied."
msgstr ""
"Constructores y pilotos de logística que mantienen las flotas abastecidas."

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "People who show up and communicate. Drama-free."
msgstr "Gente que aparece y se comunica. Sin dramas."

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "The veteran's survival guide"
msgstr "La guía de supervivencia del veterano"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"The things we all wish someone had told us on day one. Nullsec is the best "
"part of EVE — it just doesn't forgive not knowing the rules."
msgstr ""
"Las cosas que todos deseamos que alguien nos hubiera dicho el primer día. "
"Nullsec es la mejor parte de EVE: simplemente no perdona no conocer las "
"reglas."

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Ships are ammo"
msgstr "Las naves son munición"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Fly only what you can lose.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">If losing the ship would ruin your night, don't "
"undock it. Every hull you fly in null should be one you could replace "
"tomorrow without pain.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Vuela solo lo que puedas perder.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Si perder la nave te arruinaría la noche, no la "
"desatraques. Cada casco que vueles en null debería ser uno que pudieras "
"reemplazar mañana sin dolor.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Losses are tuition, not failure.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Every veteran has a killboard full of "
"embarrassing losses; that's how we all learned. Read your loss, pick one "
"thing you'd do differently, and move on.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Las pérdidas son matrícula, no fracaso."
"</span> <span class=\"text-faint\">Todo veterano tiene un killboard lleno de "
"pérdidas vergonzosas; así es como todos aprendimos. Lee tu pérdida, elige "
"una cosa que harías diferente y sigue adelante.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Insurance and SRP soften losses.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Buy platinum insurance <em>before</em> you undock "
"(right-click your ship → Insurance) — it pays back a chunk of the hull, "
"never the modules. Fly the corp's doctrine fit (our standard, pre-approved "
"fittings) on an official fleet and the Ship Replacement Program pays you "
"back too — just file your claim after.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">El seguro y el SRP suavizan las "
"pérdidas.</span> <span class=\"text-faint\">Compra el seguro platino "
"<em>antes</em> de desatracar (clic derecho en tu nave → Insurance): te "
"devuelve una parte del casco, nunca los módulos. Vuela el doctrine fit de la "
"corp (nuestros fittings estándar preaprobados) en una flota oficial y el "
"Ship Replacement Program también te reembolsa: solo presenta tu reclamación "
"después.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Keep your combat clone cheap.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">When your pod dies, the implants in your head die "
"with it. Save the shiny sets for a jump clone — a spare body you can swap "
"into; ask a vet to help you set one up.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Mantén barato tu clon de combate.</"
"span> <span class=\"text-faint\">Cuando muere tu pod, los implantes de tu "
"cabeza mueren con él. Guarda los sets caros para un jump clone: un cuerpo de "
"repuesto al que puedes cambiar; pídele a un veterano que te ayude a "
"configurar uno.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Local and d-scan are your radar"
msgstr "El local y el d-scan son tu radar"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Watch local chat always.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">In nullsec everyone in the system shows in local's "
"pilot list the moment they arrive. Keep it visible, and treat any name you "
"don't recognise as a hunter until proven otherwise.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Vigila siempre el chat local.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">En nullsec, todos los que están en el sistema "
"aparecen en la lista de pilotos del local en cuanto llegan. Mantenlo visible "
"y trata cualquier nombre que no reconozcas como un cazador hasta que se "
"demuestre lo contrario.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Make d-scan a reflex.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">The directional scanner (default V) shows most ships "
"and probes within ~14 AU — but not cloaked ships or Combat Recon cruisers, "
"so a clear scan is never a promise. Hit it every few seconds while running "
"sites or mining; combat probes on scan means align out and leave now.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Haz del d-scan un reflejo.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">El escáner direccional (V por defecto) muestra la "
"mayoría de naves y sondas dentro de ~14 AU, pero no las naves con cloak ni "
"los cruceros Combat Recon, así que un escaneo limpio nunca es una garantía. "
"Púlsalo cada pocos segundos mientras haces sites o minas; sondas de combate "
"en el escaneo significa alinéate para salir y vete ya.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Watch the intel channels.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Pilots report hostiles by system name. Learn the "
"systems around home, so a report three jumps out buys you a full minute of "
"warning instead of none.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Vigila los canales de intel.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Los pilotos reportan hostiles por nombre de "
"sistema. Aprende los sistemas alrededor de casa, para que un reporte a tres "
"saltos te dé un minuto entero de aviso en lugar de ninguno.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">When in doubt, dock up.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Docked, you are truly safe — nobody has ever died "
"docked. Tethered at a friendly structure you're repaired and protected, but "
"you can be bumped off tether and killed, so never go AFK on tether. Stepping "
"away in space? Use safe-logoff, not hope.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">En caso de duda, atraca.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Atracado, estás realmente a salvo: nadie ha muerto "
"nunca atracado. Con tether en una estructura amiga estás reparado y "
"protegido, pero pueden empujarte fuera del tether y matarte, así que nunca "
"te vayas AFK con tether. ¿Te alejas estando en el espacio? Usa safe-logoff, "
"no la esperanza.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Getting around without dying"
msgstr "Moverse sin morir"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Bubbles catch you in null.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Warp disruption bubbles stop your warp early or drag "
"you past a gate into a trap — no warning, no countdown. Inside one <em>you "
"cannot warp at all</em>: turn on your prop mod, burn for the edge (double-"
"click in space away from the wrecks), and warp somewhere else the moment "
"you're clear.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Las bubbles te atrapan en null.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Las warp disruption bubbles cortan tu warp antes "
"de tiempo o te arrastran más allá de una gate hacia una trampa: sin aviso, "
"sin cuenta atrás. Dentro de una <em>no puedes warpear en absoluto</em>: "
"activa tu prop mod, quema hacia el borde (doble clic en el espacio lejos de "
"los restos) y warpea a otro sitio en cuanto estés libre.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Never autopilot in null.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Autopilot delivers you to a gate camp like room "
"service. Fly every jump by hand, and check the corp killboard and Gate Camp "
"Watch for recent kills on your route before you commit.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Nunca uses autopiloto en null.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">El autopiloto te entrega a un gate camp como "
"servicio de habitaciones. Haz cada salto a mano y revisa el killboard de la "
"corp y Gate Camp Watch por kills recientes en tu ruta antes de comprometerte."
"</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Bookmark safes and tacticals.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">A safe spot (a bookmark made mid-warp, away from "
"anything warpable) gives you somewhere to hide and d-scan from. A tactical "
"is the same idea a few hundred km off a busy gate, so you can look before "
"you leap. Make a few of each in home systems on day one.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Guarda marcadores de safes y tácticos.</"
"span> <span class=\"text-faint\">Un safe spot (un marcador hecho a mitad de "
"warp, lejos de cualquier cosa a la que se pueda warpear) te da un sitio "
"donde esconderte y hacer d-scan. Un táctico es la misma idea a unos cientos "
"de km de una gate concurrida, para que puedas mirar antes de saltar. Haz "
"unos cuantos de cada en los sistemas de casa el primer día.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Your gate cloak buys time.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">After a jump you stay cloaked up to a minute while you "
"don't move. Never panic-warp — take a breath, read the grid; burning back to "
"the gate is often the right call.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Tu gate cloak te da tiempo.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Tras un salto permaneces con cloak hasta un "
"minuto mientras no te muevas. Nunca hagas panic-warp: respira, lee el grid; "
"quemar de vuelta a la gate suele ser la decisión correcta.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Fleet up: comms and discipline"
msgstr "A la flota: comms y disciplina"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Listen first, talk less.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">When a fight starts, voice comms belong to the FC and "
"scouts. Your question can wait; a talked-over FC gets people killed.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Escucha primero, habla menos.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Cuando empieza una pelea, los comms de voz son "
"del FC y los scouts. Tu pregunta puede esperar; un FC al que le hablan por "
"encima hace que maten a gente.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">The FC's word is final.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">A fleet doing one imperfect thing together beats thirty "
"pilots doing their own clever thing separately. Odd order? Follow it, ask "
"why after.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">La palabra del FC es definitiva.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Una flota haciendo una cosa imperfecta junta "
"supera a treinta pilotos haciendo cada uno su propia genialidad por "
"separado. ¿Orden rara? Cúmplela, pregunta por qué después.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
#, python-format
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Broadcast for reps early.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Taking damage? Hit the broadcast in the fleet window — "
"that's how logi (the fleet's healers) know to repair you. Broadcast the type "
"your doctrine tanks: shield fleet, shield button; armor fleet, armor button "
"— the FC will say which. And do it when the shooting starts, not at 10%% "
"structure.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Haz broadcast de reps pronto.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">¿Recibes daño? Pulsa el broadcast en la ventana "
"de flota: así es como los logi (los sanadores de la flota) saben que deben "
"repararte. Haz broadcast del tipo que tanquea tu doctrine: flota de escudo, "
"botón de escudo; flota de blindaje, botón de blindaje; el FC dirá cuál. Y "
"hazlo cuando empiecen los disparos, no al 10%% de estructura.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">\"X up\" means volunteer.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">When a ping says x up, type an x in the channel the "
"ping names (usually corp chat or the ops channel), ideally with the ship you "
"can bring — you'll get a fleet invite. Never be shy about x-ing up in a "
"newbro doctrine ship; that's exactly what they're for.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">\"X up\" significa apuntarse.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Cuando un ping dice x up, escribe una x en el "
"canal que indique el ping (normalmente el chat de corp o el canal de ops), "
"idealmente con la nave que puedes traer: recibirás una invitación a la "
"flota. Nunca te dé vergüenza hacer x up en una nave de doctrine para "
"newbros; para eso están exactamente.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Never AFK on a gate.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">The order to jump comes with zero warning; miss it and "
"you're alone in hostile space. Need to step away? Say so on comms first.</"
"span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Nunca estés AFK en una gate.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">La orden de saltar llega sin ningún aviso; si la "
"pierdes, estás solo en espacio hostil. ¿Necesitas ausentarte? Dilo primero "
"por comms.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Earning ISK where you live"
msgstr "Ganar ISK donde vives"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Ratting pays in ticks.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Bounties from shooting NPC pirates pay out every twenty "
"minutes — a \"tick\". Part of every bounty is skimmed into the system's ESS "
"bank, and hostiles love raiding it — an ESS warning in intel means get safe "
"like any other hostile report. Start with sites your ship comfortably "
"handles and your ticks grow with your skills.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">El ratting paga en ticks.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Las bounties por disparar a piratas NPC se pagan cada "
"veinte minutos: un \"tick\". Parte de cada bounty se desvía al banco ESS del "
"sistema, y a los hostiles les encanta asaltarlo: un aviso de ESS en el intel "
"significa ponerte a salvo como con cualquier otro reporte de hostiles. "
"Empieza con sites que tu nave maneje cómodamente y tus ticks crecen con tus "
"skills.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Mine with the fleet.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Corp mining fleets come with boosts and many extra eyes "
"on intel — you earn more and die less. A solo miner in null is bait; a fleet "
"miner is an income.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Mina con la flota.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Las flotas de minería de la corp vienen con boosts y "
"muchos ojos extra en el intel: ganas más y mueres menos. Un minero en "
"solitario en null es cebo; un minero en flota es un ingreso.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">PI is easy passive money.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Planetary Industry takes minutes of clicking per day "
"once set up and quietly pays millions. Ask in corp chat which planets in our "
"space are good.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">La PI es dinero pasivo fácil.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">La Planetary Industry lleva minutos de clics al "
"día una vez configurada y paga millones sin hacer ruido. Pregunta en el chat "
"de corp qué planetas de nuestro espacio son buenos.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Use the corp buyback.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Hauling loot to Jita through hostile space is how "
"newbros die rich. Sell to the buyback instead: slightly less on paper, zero "
"risk, ISK today.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Usa el buyback de la corp.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Transportar loot a Jita a través de espacio hostil es "
"como los newbros mueren ricos. Véndelo al buyback en su lugar: un poco menos "
"sobre el papel, cero riesgo, ISK hoy.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Ask loud, die less"
msgstr "Pregunta alto, muere menos"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">There are no stupid questions.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Only silent deaths. Every veteran here asked the "
"exact same questions once — answering them is what the help channels are for."
"</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">No hay preguntas estúpidas.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Solo muertes silenciosas. Todo veterano aquí hizo "
"exactamente las mismas preguntas alguna vez: responderlas es para lo que "
"están los canales de ayuda.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">The corp wants you undocked.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Nobody is annoyed when a newbro loses a ship on "
"fleet — we're glad you came. Join the next newbro-friendly fleet on the ops "
"board this week; showing up in a cheap doctrine ship is the whole job.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">La corp te quiere desatracado.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">A nadie le molesta que un newbro pierda una nave "
"en la flota: nos alegra que vinieras. Únete esta semana a la próxima flota "
"apta para newbros en el tablón de ops; presentarte en una nave de doctrine "
"barata es todo el trabajo.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Grab a mentor early.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Ask in corp chat for a buddy for your first fits, first "
"fleet, first ratting site. One hour with a veteran saves a month of trial "
"and error.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Consigue un mentor pronto.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Pide en el chat de corp un compañero para tus primeros "
"fits, tu primera flota, tu primer site de ratting. Una hora con un veterano "
"ahorra un mes de prueba y error.</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Speak up when things break.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Tackled (held down by enemy warp jammers so you "
"can't warp off), lost, or confused mid-op? Say so on comms immediately. An "
"FC can often save a pilot who speaks up; nobody can save the one who stays "
"quiet.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Habla cuando algo va mal.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">¿Con tackle (sujetado por warp jammers enemigos para "
"que no puedas warpear), perdido o confundido a mitad de op? Dilo por comms "
"de inmediato. Un FC a menudo puede salvar a un piloto que habla; nadie puede "
"salvar al que se queda callado.</span>"

