#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid "Learn Planetary Industry"
msgstr "Aprende Planetary Industry"

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid ""
"A five-minute primer. By the end you'll know what to build and why the "
"planner asks what it asks."
msgstr ""
"Una introducción de cinco minutos. Al terminar sabrás qué construir y por "
"qué el planificador pregunta lo que pregunta."

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid "Why bother?"
msgstr "¿Por qué molestarse?"

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid "Income while you sleep"
msgstr "Ingresos mientras duermes"

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid ""
"PI is the closest thing EVE has to passive income. Once a colony is set up "
"it keeps producing; you just reset extractors and haul. A handful of planets "
"can quietly fund your PLEX, your ammo, or a corp's fuel supply. It scales "
"from \"one planet, ten minutes a week\" to \"a factory network feeding "
"capital construction\"."
msgstr ""
"PI es lo más parecido a ingresos pasivos que hay en EVE. Una vez montada, la "
"colonia sigue produciendo; tú solo reinicias los extractores y transportas. "
"Un puñado de planetas puede pagarte tranquilamente el PLEX, la munición o el "
"combustible de la corp. Escala desde “un planeta, diez minutos a la semana” "
"hasta “una red de fábricas que alimenta la construcción de naves capital”."

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid "Two kinds of planet"
msgstr "Dos tipos de planeta"

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid "Extraction vs factory"
msgstr "Extracción vs fábrica"

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"text-ink\">Extraction planet</span> — an Extractor Control "
"Unit pulls a raw P0 resource; Basic Industry Facilities refine it into P1. "
"You export P1 (or feed it onward). Its output is set by how you place "
"extractor heads and how often you reset."
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"text-ink\">Planeta de extracción</span> — una Extractor "
"Control Unit extrae un recurso P0 en bruto; las Basic Industry Facilities lo "
"refinan en P1. Exportas P1 (o lo pasas adelante). Su producción depende de "
"cómo coloques los cabezales extractores y con qué frecuencia reinicies."

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"text-ink\">Factory planet</span> — no extraction. It imports "
"cheaper materials and combines them into higher-tier goods (P2, P3, P4). Its "
"output is set by how many factories you can fit and feed."
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"text-ink\">Planeta de fábrica</span> — sin extracción. Importa "
"materiales más baratos y los combina en bienes de nivel superior (P2, P3, "
"P4). Su producción depende de cuántas fábricas puedas instalar y alimentar."

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid "What decides your profit"
msgstr "Qué determina tu beneficio"

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid "Market price"
msgstr "Precio de mercado"

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid "Where and what you sell. The planner prices against a hub you choose."
msgstr ""
"Dónde y qué vendes. El planificador calcula precios respecto a un hub que "
"elijas."

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid "Customs (POCO) tax"
msgstr "Impuesto de aduanas (POCO)"

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid ""
"Charged every time you launch goods to/from a planet. High in hostile space."
msgstr ""
"Se cobra cada vez que lanzas bienes hacia/desde un planeta. Alto en espacio "
"hostil."

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid ""
"Getting output to market costs time or ISK — especially from null/wormhole."
msgstr ""
"Llevar la producción al mercado cuesta tiempo o ISK — especialmente desde "
"null/wormhole."

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid "Sales tax &amp; broker"
msgstr "Impuesto de ventas &amp; corretaje"

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid ""
"Market fees when you sell. Corp buyback trades a bit of margin for "
"convenience."
msgstr ""
"Comisiones de mercado al vender. El buyback de la corp cambia un poco de "
"margen por comodidad."

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid ""
"Command Grid takes all of these, applies your assumptions, and shows the "
"estimated net — with every assumption on the table so you can see exactly "
"how the number was reached."
msgstr ""
"Command Grid toma todo esto, aplica tus suposiciones y muestra el neto "
"estimado — con cada suposición sobre la mesa para que veas exactamente cómo "
"se llegó a la cifra."

#: templates/planetary/learn.html
msgid "Plan your first colony"
msgstr "Planifica tu primera colonia"

